nodes.title: Note: Model Sampling Discrete
widgets_values: If you are using a v-pred model, you may need to enable this node.

nodes.title: Note: IMG2IMG
widgets_values:
What this will do:

It will take whatever image you put above and feed it into the workflow instead of an empty latent image.

Usage example:

1. Put a screenshot from a game in the load image node and then toggle the switch for "Enable Image to Image" to true.

2. Adjust the Aspect Ratio/Resolution and the Denoise as needed. If you leave the denoise at 1.0, you will more than likely get a very different image. (TL;DR - less denoise = less change).

nodes.title: Note: Bookmarks
widgets_values:
1 - Left side of the workflow
2 - Fast Groups Bypasser
3 - Image Parameters
4 - KSampler
5 - USDU
6 - FaceDetailer
7 - Results

nodes.title: Note: Fast Groups Bypasser
widgets_values:
This is a one-stop place to toggle off groups.

The yes/no buttons toggle them on or off.

The arrow take you to the group.

Anything marked DNB - Do Not Bypass or the workflow will break.

nodes.title: Note: FaceDetailer
widgets_values:
This is basically Adetailer for comfyUI and is part of Impact-Pack. For info about it, check out their project page.

The node is called FaceDetailer, but it will work with pretty much any Detector model. (example: Eyes, Person, etc.)

UltralyticsDetectorProvider will need some sort of detection model. Some might come pre-installed with Impact-Pack, but if not, you will need to download them on your own and place them in your ComfyUI/models/Ultralytics folder in either the "bbox" or "segm" sub-folder.

SAMLoader will need a SAM model.

Place the SAM model(s) in your ComfyUI/models/sams folder.

ComfyUI Manager is the lazier/easier way if you don't want to search for the models on your own.

Just open ComfyUI Manager and click on the Model Manager.

Click on the "Type" dropdown menu and filter by either Ultralytics or sam.

After installing the models, you do need to reload comfyUI completely (unless this has changed).

If you want a full explanation on the Detailer parameters, check here: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-extension-tutorials/Main/ComfyUI-Impact-Pack/tutorial/advanced.md

TL;DR: If your face or whatever else is not being detected, lower the bbox_threshold or try a different Detector model.

Just like any part of the workflow, if you don't need this, bypass it or delete it.

nodes.title: Note: Color Correction
widgets_values:
What's this for?

Uspscaling via KSampler and/or USDU can strip some of the color out causing the end result to be less vibrant.

The settings themselves should be self-explanatory. If you don't want to use these, do the following:

1. Connect the output from the last detailer to the nodes that the Color Correct output is connected to.

2. Delete the node/group.

OR

1. Change all the settings in the Color Correct node to zero (0) except gamma if you don't want to delete.

nodes.title: Note: Detail Daemon Sampler
widgets_values:
Detail Daemon Sampler info: https://github.com/Jonseed/ComfyUI-Detail-Daemon

Video: https://youtu.be/x3AyhcH85Dg?si=bbmfSdUOXXHpolXy&t=135

What's it do?

To put it simply it tries to add more details based on what settings you put in. I use it instead of detailer loras. (Sometimes with them too).

Why do I use this?

Detailer loras sometimes cause weird things to happen. 

If you like using those loras or just don't like this node, then you can just bypass it or delete it from the workflow.

nodes.title: Note: CR SDXL Aspect Ratio
widgets_values: Self-explanatory. Pick one of the SDXL resolutions here. If you want to use a custom resolution, change aspect ratio to "Custom" and enter your width and height.

nodes.title: Note: 2nd KSampler
widgets_values:
Upscale Factor - This is based off the actual size of your initial image. (example: if your initial image is 1024x1024 and you set the Scale Factor to "2" this KSampler will upscale it to 2048x2048).

Denoise - should be self explanatory.

nodes.title: Note: Detailer Loaders
widgets_values: Do not bypass Detailer Loaders if you are using the Detailers

nodes.title: Note: Comparer Nodes
widgets_values: To use: place your cursor over the image and move left or right. That's it.

nodes.title: Note: Big lama Remover
widgets_values:
Sometimes if the watermark has a weird shape, parts of it won't be removed. In those cases, you can adjust gaussblur_radius up if needed.

If you are seeing broken images after the watermark removal portion, make sure invert_mask is set to false.

nodes.title: Note: Why 2 USDU nodes?
widgets_values:
In my own experience, USDU seems to strip out some of the details on the first pass, more noticeably the background. The 2nd pass seems to help. If you don't feel you need it, you can bypass the node istelf or delete it.

Pros: It can add more details on the 2nd pass.

Cons: Higher chance of weird results (random limbs, etc.)

Using a different upscaler model, changing the tile size, adjusting the denoise, using different samplers/schedulers all can affect how USDU behaves just like any other setting.

nodes.title: Note: Watermark Removal
widgets_values:
If you are using a model that NEVER has any watermarks/signatures, then just delete this whole section or bypass it.

For those occassions where they do show up: this part of the workflow will try to detect and remove it. Unfortunately, there are some cases where it just won't detect it.

Something will show up in the Watermark Detection Mask node if it detects what it thinks is a watermark.

TL;DR Lower threshold = more aggressive detection.

If you are getting false detections, adjust the Detection Threshold up in the Watermark Removal CLIPSeg group. (example: 0.9 or 1)

If your watermark is not being detected, adjust it down. (example: 0.0001)

If it's detecting it but giving you garbage you can try to tweak the denoise on the Watermark Removal node in the Watermark Removal Detailer Section.

Modifed version of: https://civitai.com/models/265571/dynamic-watermark-removal-during-render-or-image-upload-by-leinad882

The CLIPSegDetectorProvider in the original requires you to install an un-maintained custom node which is not in my version of the watermark workflow.

I kept the alternative Watermark removal flow below. If you want to use it instead, you will have to bypass or delete the other Watermark Removal groups and connect the image output from the Big lama Remover to the first Color Match at the "image_target" input.

nodes.title: Note: SamplerCustom
widgets_values:
These settings should be self-explanatory as well unless this is your first time generating an image or using comfyUI.

The manual for this node can be found at:

https://comfyui-wiki.com/en/comfyui-nodes/sampling/custom-sampling/sampler-custom

nodes.title: Note: Detailer
widgets_values:
If you are using this as an Eye Detailer: it sometimes helps to add your eye prompts here in the wildcard spec field. This is especially true if the eyes are being changed into something that are not eyes.

Example: detailed eyes, red eyes

nodes.title: Note: CR Seed
widgets_values:
This is now connected to all nodes that have a "seed" except the wilcard nodes. Connecting it to the wildcard nodes causes issues. You can manually set the seed to fixed on the wildcard node separately if needed.

You can set this to fixed, randomize, increment, and decrement.

If you need a explanation on what a seed you can check here:

https://www.runcomfy.com/comfyui-nodes/was-node-suite-comfyui/Seed

nodes.title: Note: Color Match
widgets_values:
If you don't want to use this node, do the following:

1. Take the input noodle for image_target and connect it to "image" input for USDU.

2. Delete the node/group.

nodes.title: Note: ControlNet
widgets_values:
Not really a big user of CN, but I do find it useful sometimes. This group can be bypassed with no problems.

Note: You might have to drop an image in the Load Image node even if you are not using this group.

nodes.title: Note: How to use LoRAs with these nodes
widgets_values:
1. Click on the "Select to add LoRA" field.
2. Click on your LoRA. This will add the lora to the prompt like in A1111.
3. Add the weight of the lora to the end of the LoRA name.

Example: <I_AM_A_LoRA:0.7>

More info on this node can be found at: https://comfyui-wiki.com/en/comfyui-nodes/sampling/custom-sampling/sampler-custom

nodes.title: Note: PAG
widgets_values:
For information on Perturbed-Attention Guidance:

https://github.com/pamparamm/sd-perturbed-attention?tab=readme-ov-file#perturbed-attention-guidance-smoothed-energy-guidance-and-sliding-window-guidance-for-comfyui--sd-webui-forgereforge

TL;DR - Your CFG + the "scale" setting below should equal the total of what you would (roughly) normally have for CFG. 

ComfyUI-ppm suggests that if you are using this with CFG++SamplerSelect to set the "scale" from 0.5 to 1.0.

If you are using a sampler that would normally use CFG 7, then you could do something like CFG 4 + scale 3.

From what I have read, going higher than scale 3 can burn the image. YMMV.

nodes.title: Note: PAG Settings
widgets_values:
Defaults:

sigma_start: -1
sigma_end: -1
rescale: 0

Settings from other users:

Realistic:

sigma_start: 3.10
sigma_end: 0.17
rescale: 0.85

Anime:

sigma_start: 5.75
sigma_end: 0.75
rescale: 0.5

nodes.title: Note: Ultimate SD Upscale
widgets_values:
If you are going bigger than 2x, I recommend increasing the mask blur and tile padding. You can use less/more, these are just my recommendations.

Example:

For 2x
mask blur: 16
tile padding: 64

For 3x
mask blur: 32
tile padding: 128

I use denoise at 0.2 to 0.4, but your mileage may vary depending on sampler/scheduler.

I normally use seam_fix_mode: "Half Tile", but you can set it to "None" for faster generation.

Details about the parameters for USDU can be found here:

https://github.com/Coyote-A/ultimate-upscale-for-automatic1111/wiki/FAQ#parameters-descriptions

The "upscale_by" setting is going to upscale according to whatever the image being fed into the input is. If the image going in is 1024x1024 and you set this to upscale_by 2.0, it should upscale it to 2048x2048. Comfy does math weird sometimes, so if you get some weird resolution, ask the comfyui devs or the dev for USDU why.

nodes.title: Note: CR Hires Fix Process Switch
widgets_values: Added this just to give the option to "upscale" on the 2nd KSampler with either Latent Upscaling or via Image Upscaling with Upscale Model. The upscale model will still go through the process, but depending on what is set here, will determine the latent input on the 2nd KSampler.
